From 47f4b50d6e89a0bdeadb73581d14a191c7c15ba9 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Marcello Sylvester Bauer <marcello.bauer@9elements.com>
Date: Sun, 15 Feb 2026 13:18:18 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] dbus: skip zone rebuild on sensor removal

Skip zone rebuilds triggered by InterfacesRemoved signals on sensor
paths. When PECI sensors disappear from D-Bus (e.g. during host power
transitions), the running PID loop already handles missing sensors
gracefully via timeout and InputUnavailableAsFailed. Rebuilding the
zone on sensor removal destroys the running control loop, leaving fans
uncontrolled until the rebuild completes.

Signed-off-by: Marcello Sylvester Bauer <marcello.bauer@9elements.com>
---
 dbus/dbusconfiguration.cpp | 13 ++++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 12 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/dbus/dbusconfiguration.cpp b/dbus/dbusconfiguration.cpp
index da8d316..47b3c1b 100644
--- a/dbus/dbusconfiguration.cpp
+++ b/dbus/dbusconfiguration.cpp
@@ -189,7 +189,18 @@ int eventHandler(sd_bus_message* m, void* context, sd_bus_error*)
             interface};
 
     sdbusplus::message_t message(m);
-    if (std::string(message.get_member()) == "InterfacesAdded")
+    std::string member = message.get_member();
+
+    // Sensor removal does not require a zone rebuild — the PID loop
+    // handles missing sensors gracefully via timeout and
+    // InputUnavailableAsFailed.  Rebuilding on removal causes unnecessary
+    // fan speed spikes during PECI sensor flicker.
+    if (member == "InterfacesRemoved")
+    {
+        return 1;
+    }
+
+    if (member == "InterfacesAdded")
     {
         sdbusplus::message::object_path path;
         std::unordered_map<
